<br>
Clearly they don't intend to do that so what is left?  The guild tag that you are so fond of is nothing more than a moniker which may represent a great deal of things, but ultimately, it's nothing more than a symbol.  What you have as a guild is what you carry inside.  I doubt seriously that will change if you join opposing guilds for a few hours of fun and mayhem.  Well, it may change if that is the sum total of your strength.  I'm thinking it's not.<br>
<br>
Why not belly up to the bar and use the suggestion as was made by another person before I added my comments?  It gives you EVERYTHING you want in the ability to meet this raid challenge in a manner fitting of the server and the players.<br>
<br>
As for my 'attacks' on Tinkers Pride members...   I would actually happily extend this attack upon anyone who made suggestions that go outside of the spirit of the game and in turn end up lessening the fun for everyone involved.  <br>
<br>
It just so happens that Xianya has put forth the strongest cry for using the LAG measure rather than the components that already are in place for such things.  The squeaky wheel gets the grease. *s<br>
